name: r-markdown-documentation
description: Comprehensive collection of well-organized and informative R Markdown documents. This repository serves as a valuable resource for anyone seeking to learn or improve their skills in creating dynamic, reproducible, and visually appealing reports and documents using R Markdown.

name: Simple-K-Means-Clustering
description: This document features clustering a wine data set. This analysis looks at the 'Colour Intensity' and 'Flavinoids' variables in the data set and is a simple demonstration of how the K-Means method can be used to cluster data in real life.

name: ETCD_Backup_Using_Snapshot
description: Etcd snapshots provide a convenient and efficient way to capture the current state of the cluster’s key-value store at a particular moment in time.

name: Information_Vizualization
description: This project builds a streaming content dashboard to visualize data on popular shows from Netflix, Hulu, Disney+, and Amazon Prime. It also uses K-Means clustering to create a recommendation system for similar movies based on user watch history.

name: Diet-Planner-with-Unsupervised-learning-and-LLMs
description: Training a K-means clustering model to predict the weight status of a patient and then plan his/her diet, using LLM's, accordingly.

name: SQL_Managing-data
description: Diving into the world of databases, which serve as the backbone of most big data projects. I'll start by understanding the basics of how databases function and progress to designing and running my own databases. This is a clear overview of how I utilise SQL and its importance in efficiently managing and manipulating data.
